|title=Eugene Palmer Added to Ten Most Wanted Fugitives List|date=28 May 2019|access-date=28 May 2019|work=[[FBI]] |publisher=[[U.S. government]], [[U.S. Department of Justice]]}}</ref>\n|-\n|2013\n|[[Lo Fu-chu]]\n|69\n|{{Flag|Taiwan}}\n|Fu-chu, a [[Taiwanese indigenous peoples|Taiwanese]] politician<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/in-taiwan-gangsters-dont-just-bribe-politicians--they-become-them-2012-6|title=In Taiwan, Gangsters Don't Just Bribe Politicians \u2013 They Become Them|last=Nunns|first=Cain|website=Business Insider|access-date=2020-01-03}}</ref> was at one time a \"Celestial Alliance\" organized criminal organization. On 28 March 2013, Lo was convicted of [[stock manipulation]], money laundering, and insider trading and was sentenced to four years in jail and fined NT$6 million (US$200,000). Later he was released on a NT$10 million (US$330,000) bond, but then failed to report to police on 24 April 2013 when he was to start his sentence. He is believed to have fled to either the United States, Australia, or China,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pri.org/stories/2012-06-08/taiwanese-politics-gangsters-paradise|title=Taiwanese politics: gangsters\u2019 paradise?|website=Public Radio International|language=en|access-date=2020-01-03}}</ref> where he has many relatives and friends, but this is unknown for sure.\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2013-01-19\"|2013\n|[[Fausto Isidro Meza Flores]]\n|30\n|{{Flag|Mexico}}\n|Mexican drug lord and high-ranking leader of the [[Beltr\u00e1n Leyva Cartel]]. The FBI offered a US$5 million bounty for information regarding his whereabouts.<ref>[https://www.fbi.gov/wanted/cei/fausto-isidro-meza-flores FBI Most Wanted: Fausto Isidro Meza-Flores]. FBI. Accessed: 19 November 2018.</ref> His last known residence was in the state of [[Nuevo Le\u00f3n]], where he was reportedly seen with some of his family members at a youth basketball game in [[San Pedro Garza Garc\u00eda]] on 19 January 2013.<ref>{{cite news|last=Cedillo |first=Juan |title=El rival de 'El Chapo' se\u00f1alado por EU no tiene cargos en M\u00e9xico |url=http://mexico.cnn.com/nacional/2013/01/21/el-rival-de-el-chapo-senalado-por-eu-no-tiene-cargos-en-mexico |accessdate=22 January 2013 |newspaper=CNNM\u00e9xico |date=21 January 2013 |agency=[[Turner Broadcasting System]] |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6Dr5Z7GjO?url=http://mexico.cnn.com/nacional/2013/01/21/el-rival-de-el-chapo-senalado-por-eu-no-tiene-cargos-en-mexico |archivedate=22 January 2013 |url-status=live |language=Spanish |df=mdy }}</ref>\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2013-08-09\"|2013\n|[[Rafael Caro Quintero]]\n|61\n|{{Flag|Mexico}}\n|Caro Quintero, a [[Mexican people|Mexican]] [[Illegal drug trade in Latin America|drug trafficker]], was convicted in Mexico of murdering a US [[Drug Enforcement Administration]] (DEA) agent. He was freed from jail on 9 August 2013 after a court concluded that he had been tried improperly. Amid pressure from the Federal government of the United States to re-arrest him, a Mexican federal court issued an arrest warrant against Caro Quintero on 14 August 2013. He is a wanted fugitive in Mexico, the United States and several other countries. The United States is offering a $20 million bounty for his arrest.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2013/aug/15/mexican-judge-warrant-arrest-rafael-caro-quintero|title=Mexican judge issues warrant for arrest of freed drugs baron|last=Tuckman|first=Jo|date=15 August 2013|website=the Guardian|language=en|access-date=30 August 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|2014\n|[[Serhiy Kurchenko]]\n|28\n|{{Flag|Ukraine}}\n|Kurchenko, a [[Ukrainians|Ukrainian]] businessman and the founder and owner of the group of companies that specialize in trading of [[liquefied natural gas]]. He achieved success and a young age as he is also the former owner and president of [[FC Metalist Kharkiv]] and the Ukrainian Media Holding group. He is currently on the international wanted list.<ref name=\"totaling over U